examples.en: He felt he was on the edge of an abyss.
The country might plunge into the abyss of economic ruin.
How big is the abyss between what you think you are and what you actually are?
At that time Bosnia was standing on the edge of an abyss.
Looking down at the dark ocean from the ship's rail, the cruise passenger felt as though he was staring into an abyss.
